@Lea 

What I love about a rebus is that it forces me to access information from my "filing cabinet" in a different manner.  I think part of my internal filing system relates to the length of a word, so when I know how long a word is going to be, it makes it easier to find the correct one.  A rebus makes me stretch and use other methods.  

I started doing the NYTXW in October 2016, so my first rebus was 11/3/16.  It was like a revelation.  Luckily, it was a gentle rebus, but still, I had no idea such a thing existed.  "Do they really expect me to do this?"  "I guess so, because I can't see another way to get this done!" I was strictly a paper solver and waited until the next day to find out that I was indeed expected to do that.  The scales fell from my eyes.  It was love at first sight.

